The paper deals with parallel aggregation, which is a common operation in data analytics. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a mathematical model and algorithm for optimizing aggregation plans, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
